The paper deals with a geometric optimization problem involving rectangles in the plane, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The problem is shown to be NP-hard and APX-hard, indicating that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms for geometric set cover problems, which suggests that it may be relevant to the sub-categories of graph theory (cs.GT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
